  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PA for Formulating a comprehensive TA Program for supporting the competitiveness of the Ethiopian textile industry</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As a follow up of the &#x201C;High Level MoI-UNIDO Planning Meeting - Manufacturing Sector&#x201D; held in Addis Ababa the 14 December 2016, the UNIDO team has received clear instructions from the Ethiopian Ministry of Industry regarding activities to be performed in 2017 within the framework of the PCP-ETH. In this context, the State Minister of Industry H.E. Bogale Feleke officially requested  UNIDO to perform a PA in order to design a TA program for Textile and Garment  in the three following areas of intervention (T&amp;G sector):
 &#x2022;Component one: production, quality and competitiveness enhancement;
&#x2022; Component two: product diversification from the raw material up to the marketing;
&#x2022;Component three: institutional capacity building to the Ministry of Industry and the Ethiopian Textile Industry Development Institute (ETIDI).
In this context, the general objective of  this PA is to support an inclusive and sustainable industrial development of the Ethiopian textile sector.</narrative>
  </description>
